Be aware that using "as" here can hide index errors.  If you accidentally use `sqlreader[indexAge] as string ?? ""`, you'll always get `""`.  Consider whether you really want `(int?)sqlreader[indexAge] ?? defaultValue` instead, so if your SQL changes you get exceptions instead of bad values.

